*.pyc
*.pyo
src/__pycache__/
src/baselines/__pycache__/
src/env/__pycache__/
src/wrappers/__pycache__/
src/models/__pycache__/
src/train/__pycache__/
src/eval/__pycache__/

# --- Editor / OS junk ---
.vscode/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Jupyter ---
notebooks/eda/.ipynb_checkpoints/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# --- Experiment tracking (regenerable by rerunning training) ---
mlflow.db
mlruns/
lightning_logs/

# --- Trained RL models: too large for plain git, use Git LFS if you need them tracked ---
# (comment the line below out and run `git lfs track "runs/**/*.zip"` if you decide to keep them)
runs/

# --- Regenerable caches ---
results/forecasts/*.pkl

# --- NOTE: raw per-seed sensitivity/ablation/trace CSVs under results/ are TRACKED, not ignored.
# Decision (per student): panel may want raw per-seed data for reproducibility, and results/
# is only ~72MB total, so the whole results/ tree is committed except caches below.

# --- Old superseded / debug scripts and logs ---
overnight_trackb_*.log
*.zip
!README.md

# --- mlflow backups ---
mlflow.db.backup*

# --- Miscellaneous stray files seen in git status ---
Get-ExecutionPolicy
git_status.txt
git_status_current.txt

# --- Reference/literature PDFs: these are cited papers, not your output. Don't commit to code repo. ---
Performance analysis of AI-based energy management*.pdf
Anchor*.pdf
Main_Anchor*.pdf

# === Explicitly DO track (documented here so nothing above accidentally excludes these) ===
# results/                    <-- ENTIRE tree tracked (figures, tables, analysis, ablation, phase3,
#                                  sensitivity sweeps incl. tank/lognormal, traces) — ~72MB total,
#                                  kept for reproducibility per student decision (2026-07-08)
# final_thesis_numbers*.txt
# reviewer_comment2_checklist.md
# reviewer_comment3_reward_justification.md
# analyse_rlinv_da_v2.py, check_*.py, plot_*.py  <-- all your analysis scripts
# traces/                     <-- root-level traces folder, same reproducibility rationale

check_*.csv
check_*.npz
test_*.csv
runs_*.txt
phase3_*_tree.txt
test.py

demo_run_output*.csv
